1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:06,339
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:14,639
[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:21,020
[Lorna] For now, I need someone
to guard the gold card area.

4
00:00:21,104 --> 00:00:22,439
[Atoy] Ma'am, I'll do it.

5
00:00:22,522 --> 00:00:25,024
You can't. You're new.

6
00:00:25,108 --> 00:00:26,443
You might mess things up there.

7
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:30,488
The customers there tip big,
especially those betting on fights.

8
00:00:30,572 --> 00:00:32,240
[Atoy] <i>What? Boxing, like that?</i>

9
00:00:32,323 --> 00:00:33,450
[janitor] <i>But the ones fighting</i>
<i>are little people.</i>

10
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:34,784
<i>It's brutal.</i>

11
00:00:34,868 --> 00:00:36,202
PREVIOUSLY

12
00:00:36,286 --> 00:00:41,124
[Darryl] No one else can help you
get out of here but yourself.

13
00:00:41,207 --> 00:00:43,418
[in English] Red, how are you?

14
00:00:43,501 --> 00:00:47,088
[Vladimir, in English] <i>How about we find</i>
<i>a place where we can meet Manny Pacquiao?</i>

15
00:00:47,172 --> 00:00:48,173
[in English] <i>You know any?</i>

16
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:49,257
[Red, in English] <i>I actually know a place.</i>

17
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:50,842
[Vladimir, in English] <i>Oh, let's go.</i>

18
00:00:50,925 --> 00:00:55,430
[Ibyang] I hope he finds Big Sister Ame,
so I can leave this place.

19
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:56,765
[Vladimir, in English]
<i>What is this place, Red?</i>

20
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:58,850
[Red, in English]
You're gonna love this place.

21
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:02,937
[in English] It's a, uh,
battle of mini gladiators.

22
00:01:03,021 --> 00:01:08,693
[Cita] <i>Your Brother Atoy will never stop</i>
<i>until he finds your Big Sis Ame.</i>

23
00:01:08,777 --> 00:01:10,779
- [Cita] <i>That's the kind of person he is.</i>
- [clatters]

24
00:01:10,862 --> 00:01:12,989
- That's been going on for a while.
- [waiter, in English] Sorry, sir!

25
00:01:13,073 --> 00:01:14,824
[waiter] There's someone
messing around here.

26
00:01:16,534 --> 00:01:20,121
[curious upbeat music playing]

27
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:23,583
[MC, in English] And for our next fight,

28
00:01:23,666 --> 00:01:28,421
it's going to be a rematch
between two rivals.

29
00:01:28,505 --> 00:01:33,426
Now, they are going to settle the score.

30
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:38,515
It's a fight to the death with

31
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:43,937
- Tessie Bangis
- [crowd cheering]

32
00:01:44,020 --> 00:01:45,522
versus

33
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:49,818
The Amazing Ame!

34
00:01:49,901 --> 00:01:52,028
[crowd cheering and applauding]

35
00:01:52,570 --> 00:01:55,990
[MC, in English]
Who will emerge as the winner?

36
00:01:56,074 --> 00:02:00,662
- [curious upbeat music continues]
- [phone keys tapping]

37
00:02:01,913 --> 00:02:03,331
Hello?

38
00:02:03,414 --> 00:02:05,333
Where are you? Are you okay?
Are you out of the hospital?

39
00:02:05,416 --> 00:02:07,418
Boss Red, why?

40
00:02:07,502 --> 00:02:08,753
What do you mean why?

41
00:02:08,837 --> 00:02:11,256
I'm here at Endless. Come here!

42
00:02:12,215 --> 00:02:15,885
Okay, Boss, I'll follow.
I just need to collect something.

43
00:02:18,054 --> 00:02:19,139
Hello?

44
00:02:19,222 --> 00:02:21,015
[crowd buzzing]

45
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:32,235
[tense music playing]

46
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:36,447
- [curious upbeat music playing]
- [crowd cheering]

47
00:02:38,449 --> 00:02:39,325
[woman] Sir.

48
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:43,204
[ref] Are you ready?

49
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:45,039
Are you ready?

50
00:02:45,123 --> 00:02:47,542
Since yesterday, Boss. Let's do this.

51
00:02:47,625 --> 00:02:48,835
[ref] Touch glove.

52
00:02:51,337 --> 00:02:52,714
- [ref] Box.
- [bell dings]

53
00:02:52,797 --> 00:02:55,550
I'm really going to finish you now.

54
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:57,510
[brazen music playing]

55
00:02:57,594 --> 00:02:59,095
[whooshing]

56
00:02:59,178 --> 00:03:00,930
[crowd gasps, whistles, cheers]

57
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:05,143
[in English] Yes! I love it!

58
00:03:05,226 --> 00:03:06,394
[in English] This is good!

59
00:03:06,477 --> 00:03:09,480
[crowd clamoring]

60
00:03:12,483 --> 00:03:13,443
[crowd gasps, buzzing]

61
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:15,570
[brazen music continues]

62
00:03:15,653 --> 00:03:18,615
[whooshing]

63
00:03:27,540 --> 00:03:29,584
- [in English] This is very, very good!
- [crowd cheering]

64
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:30,793
[laughs]

65
00:03:40,428 --> 00:03:42,222
That Atoy lives here.

66
00:03:42,305 --> 00:03:44,140
[inquisitive music playing]

67
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:49,020
I know someone who can make him obey.

68
00:03:53,524 --> 00:03:54,609
Oh, gosh.

69
00:03:54,692 --> 00:03:56,152
Do it, please.

70
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,237
[waiter] Sorry, sir.

71
00:03:57,320 --> 00:04:00,031
[Atoy, in English] Oh, no.
It's okay, sir, we'll help you.

72
00:04:00,114 --> 00:04:03,159
- [patron] Go on, carry him.
- [Atoy] I'll get a mop.

73
00:04:03,243 --> 00:04:04,285
[patron] Go on, hurry up.

74
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:08,414
[suave music playing]

75
00:04:34,023 --> 00:04:35,692
[crowd cheering]

76
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:38,945
[brazen music playing]

77
00:04:39,028 --> 00:04:40,405
[in English] Finish her!

78
00:04:40,488 --> 00:04:41,364
[thuds]

79
00:04:41,447 --> 00:04:42,532
[in English] Finish her now!

80
00:04:42,615 --> 00:04:43,616
[crowd cheering]

81
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:48,496
Agh! [in English] I love it!
I love the Philippines!

82
00:04:48,579 --> 00:04:50,206
[laughs]

83
00:04:50,290 --> 00:04:51,916
Yes! Whoo!

84
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,419
- One! Two!
- [crowd cheering]

85
00:04:54,502 --> 00:04:56,713
Three! Four!

86
00:04:56,796 --> 00:05:01,342
Five! Six! Seven!

87
00:05:01,426 --> 00:05:03,845
Eight! Nine!

88
00:05:05,221 --> 00:05:06,472
- Ten!
- [bell dinging]

89
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:09,434
[MC, in English] We have a winner!

90
00:05:09,517 --> 00:05:12,645
The Amazing Ame!

91
00:05:12,729 --> 00:05:17,108
- [brazen music playing]
- [crowd cheering]

92
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:18,693
[in English] Nice win!

93
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:20,194
Oh!

94
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,407
- [in English] You liked it, huh?
- [in English] I love it!

95
00:05:24,490 --> 00:05:25,700
[in English] I love the Philippines!

96
00:05:25,783 --> 00:05:27,076
- [Red chuckles]
- Whoo!

97
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:31,289
[crowd applauding]

98
00:05:31,372 --> 00:05:37,295
[melancholic music playing]

99
00:05:42,425 --> 00:05:43,760
[in English] I love this girl.

100
00:05:44,802 --> 00:05:45,636
[in English] Who is she?

101
00:05:47,263 --> 00:05:49,724
[in English] Oh, Amazing Ame, yes.

102
00:05:49,807 --> 00:05:52,769
[crowd whistling, applauding]

103
00:06:01,652 --> 00:06:02,737
[gasps]

104
00:06:04,322 --> 00:06:05,364
[in English] Listen, Red.

105
00:06:05,948 --> 00:06:08,993
[in English] I want to meet
the Amazing Ame.

106
00:06:09,952 --> 00:06:12,038
[in English] Okay, I can
make arrangements. Don't worry.

107
00:06:12,121 --> 00:06:13,081
[in English] Very good, very good.

108
00:06:13,164 --> 00:06:16,250
[in English] It's because I have
a Japanese client.

109
00:06:17,168 --> 00:06:19,295
- [in English] Very, very rich.
- [in English] Okay.

110
00:06:19,378 --> 00:06:21,339
[in English] And he's into midgets!

111
00:06:21,422 --> 00:06:22,381
[laughs]

112
00:06:23,299 --> 00:06:25,968
[in English] We say "little persons" here
in the Philippines, okay?

113
00:06:26,052 --> 00:06:28,054
- [in English] That's the rule, okay?
- [in English] Okay.

114
00:06:28,137 --> 00:06:29,722
[in English] But okay,
let's talk business.

115
00:06:29,806 --> 00:06:31,224
[in English] Okay, good.

116
00:06:31,307 --> 00:06:32,350
[in English] The gameplan…

117
00:06:33,142 --> 00:06:35,478
[in English] If you
can give me Amazing Ame,

118
00:06:36,145 --> 00:06:39,690
I promise you it'll be worth your while.

119
00:06:39,774 --> 00:06:42,026
Because it's very hard to find

120
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:46,531
a "little person"
with a beautiful, pretty face like hers,

121
00:06:46,614 --> 00:06:48,741
- Right?
- [laughs]

122
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:51,327
[in English] Don't worry.
I can make that happen.

123
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:52,620
I'll take care of that for you.

124
00:06:52,703 --> 00:06:54,413
- [in English] This is it. I love you!
- [laughs]

125
00:06:54,497 --> 00:06:56,707
- [in English] Yes, I love the Philippines!
- [in English] Hey, hey, hey!

126
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:58,376
[in English] Don't forget
my finder's fee, okay?

127
00:06:58,459 --> 00:06:59,836
- [in English] I got you.
- [in English] Good.

128
00:06:59,919 --> 00:07:01,546
- [in English] Cheers!
- [chuckles]

129
00:07:03,214 --> 00:07:04,257
[Vladimir gasps]

130
00:07:04,340 --> 00:07:05,633
[laughs]

131
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:07,718
- [in English] My man, my man.
- [in English] Yes.

132
00:07:09,470 --> 00:07:11,097
[Paldo] One of those, Miss Siony.

133
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,598
- Just one?
- Just one, just one.

134
00:07:13,641 --> 00:07:14,559
[Paldo] That's it!

135
00:07:15,101 --> 00:07:16,853
- So, bro, you want one?
- Go ahead.

136
00:07:17,353 --> 00:07:18,896
Just soft drinks for me, sis.

137
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:20,314
How many? What kind of soft drinks?

138
00:07:20,398 --> 00:07:22,233
Whatever is cold. Anything you got.

139
00:07:25,236 --> 00:07:29,991
[phone ringing]

140
00:07:33,995 --> 00:07:36,247
[inquisitive music playing]

141
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:37,415
[man] Mongki?

142
00:07:37,498 --> 00:07:39,917
Isn't that the guy you sold the statue to?

143
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:45,339
Why don't you want to answer?
Maybe it's good sign.

144
00:07:46,841 --> 00:07:47,884
Does he owe you money?

145
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:49,635
I don't want to deal with him anymore.

146
00:07:50,928 --> 00:07:53,806
You know, I regret
ever meeting these people.

147
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:55,892
Maybe that's another hustle.

148
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:00,354
It's fine if it's just a hustle.

149
00:08:02,523 --> 00:08:05,026
But if innocent people got implicated…

150
00:08:05,902 --> 00:08:07,361
Huh? What are you saying?

151
00:08:07,445 --> 00:08:10,198
- [tires screeching]
- [thuds]

152
00:08:12,825 --> 00:08:15,036
Boss, that might be Atoy's father.

153
00:08:15,119 --> 00:08:16,287
[Paldo] You might have killed him.

154
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:17,663
Boss, he had no beef with us.

155
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:24,754
This imbecile Paldo,
he's really unreliable.

156
00:08:26,172 --> 00:08:27,173
So, what now, Boss?

157
00:08:27,256 --> 00:08:29,675
Tabang Lupa is quite big.

158
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:30,635
So, what?

159
00:08:30,718 --> 00:08:32,512
You don't want revenge anymore?

160
00:08:32,595 --> 00:08:34,430
Then I'll just look for him myself! Go on!

161
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:35,640
- Go on, leave!
- [thug 1] It's not like that, Boss.

162
00:08:35,723 --> 00:08:37,642
- We want to make up for it.
- Then there you go!

163
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:39,018
You talk too much.

164
00:08:39,101 --> 00:08:40,853
Let's go!

165
00:08:40,937 --> 00:08:41,854
[man] Hmm…

166
00:08:41,938 --> 00:08:45,441
- What? You like it?
- [in English] Thank you!

167
00:08:46,025 --> 00:08:47,652
[in English] Good. Welcome.

168
00:08:47,735 --> 00:08:50,321
Now, call Georgia.

169
00:08:50,404 --> 00:08:52,698
I have a gift for her too, okay?

170
00:08:52,782 --> 00:08:54,534
Don't be jealous.

171
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:56,118
You both have one anyway.

172
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:58,412
Go on. Go on.

173
00:08:58,496 --> 00:09:00,081
- [in English] Okay.
- [in English] Okay, good.

174
00:09:00,164 --> 00:09:01,123
[in English] Bye.

175
00:09:01,999 --> 00:09:08,339
[inquisitive music playing]

176
00:09:14,303 --> 00:09:15,763
[in English] What the hell?

177
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:19,016
[in English] Someone stole
my freaking jacket!

178
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:21,227
Yes, sir? Is there a problem?

179
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:22,603
Someone took my jacket.

180
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:24,939
There's a Rolex in the pocket. Goddamnit!

181
00:09:25,022 --> 00:09:27,525
Who? A customer?

182
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:29,068
[in English] No.

183
00:09:31,070 --> 00:09:33,906
I think it was the janitor
who was here earlier.

184
00:09:34,574 --> 00:09:36,492
The one who wiped the spilled drink.

185
00:09:36,576 --> 00:09:38,119
Which one of them?

186
00:09:38,202 --> 00:09:39,412
We have many janitors here.

187
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:42,081
[in English] Stupid question!
Of course, I don't know!

188
00:09:42,707 --> 00:09:45,209
[in English] I want my jacket back now!

189
00:09:45,293 --> 00:09:47,878
[in English] I pay a premium
yearly membership here!

190
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:51,173
Okay, sir. I'll have
the security guys check on it.

191
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:52,592
- Okay!
- Sorry, sir.

192
00:09:53,509 --> 00:09:57,430
[brazen music playing]

193
00:10:02,935 --> 00:10:06,731
[Atoy] That's good.

194
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:18,034
[inquisitive music playing]

195
00:10:25,541 --> 00:10:27,668
We're being called to the main room.

196
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:29,462
Huh? Why?

197
00:10:30,463 --> 00:10:31,589
A customer is complaining.

198
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:33,174
Something is missing.

199
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:35,885
- Is that so?
- Yes.

200
00:10:35,968 --> 00:10:36,886
Okay, I'll follow.

201
00:10:37,928 --> 00:10:41,682
[foreboding music playing]

202
00:10:50,858 --> 00:10:51,942
- Sis…
- Mmm?

203
00:10:52,026 --> 00:10:54,487
Miss Cita's new bed spacer is pretty.

204
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:56,364
Oh, you like her?

205
00:10:56,447 --> 00:10:58,824
Just because I find her pretty,
you think I like her?

206
00:10:58,908 --> 00:11:00,326
- I'm choosy, you know!
- [indistinct]

207
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:02,578
- The green one, cold.
- But you're right, she's pretty.

208
00:11:02,662 --> 00:11:05,206
- They say she's from Cebu. Mmm-hmm!
- [girl] Cebu?

209
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:08,626
- Isn't Emerson from Cebu too?
- [girl] That's how it works…

210
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:11,712
Yes, but it's been a while
since I went home.

211
00:11:11,796 --> 00:11:13,255
But you still have relatives there.

212
00:11:13,339 --> 00:11:15,257
Your siblings are still there, right?

213
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:21,514
[uneasy music playing]

214
00:11:30,272 --> 00:11:31,107
Just asking.

215
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:32,149
- [woman 1] Ouch.
- [woman 2] Huh? What's that?

216
00:11:32,233 --> 00:11:33,150
Do you know Atoy?

217
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:34,652
[Mongki] You?

218
00:11:34,735 --> 00:11:36,654
Wait, wait, wait…

219
00:11:36,737 --> 00:11:38,280
You, don't act tough in front of me, okay?

220
00:11:39,031 --> 00:11:39,949
You don't know me.

221
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:41,200
That's the thing.

222
00:11:41,283 --> 00:11:43,077
You're not from here.

223
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,496
Bunda, who's your enemy?

224
00:11:45,579 --> 00:11:46,497
[Bunda] Well, it's this one--

225
00:11:46,580 --> 00:11:48,999
- [thuds]
- [clamoring]

226
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,501
[cheering] What?! Feels good?!

227
00:11:50,584 --> 00:11:52,086
Huh?! What?! Huh, huh?!

228
00:11:53,212 --> 00:11:55,214
[clamoring]

229
00:11:56,090 --> 00:11:57,591
[thudding]

230
00:11:57,675 --> 00:12:02,847
[intense music playing]

231
00:12:04,014 --> 00:12:05,599
You're so fierce, Ame.

232
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:07,601
You're terrifying.

233
00:12:08,853 --> 00:12:10,396
Thank you, Darryl.

234
00:12:11,021 --> 00:12:15,901
If not for you, I wouldn't have
learned how to fight in the ring.

235
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:20,531
I'm happy I was able
to help you, even just a little.

236
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:22,658
[door clicks open]

237
00:12:22,741 --> 00:12:24,702
[uneasy music playing]

238
00:12:24,785 --> 00:12:25,786
[MC] Get ready.

239
00:12:26,620 --> 00:12:28,247
You have another fight, Ame.

240
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:30,666
Who will I be fighting?

241
00:12:30,749 --> 00:12:32,293
That one, Darryl.

242
00:12:38,007 --> 00:12:39,967
Do they really do that here?

243
00:12:40,050 --> 00:12:41,469
Woman against man?

244
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:44,889
We don't have a choice
but to follow orders.

245
00:12:44,972 --> 00:12:48,601
[uneasy music continues]

246
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:50,561
Don't hold back, Ame.

247
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:52,229
Knock me down.

248
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:55,232
I won't do that.

249
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:57,735
This could be your tenth win,

250
00:12:57,818 --> 00:13:00,821
and if that happens,
you'll be able to leave this place.

251
00:13:01,530 --> 00:13:05,618
You need to win
because your father needs you.

252
00:13:05,701 --> 00:13:10,039
If I win, we won't see each other again.

253
00:13:10,122 --> 00:13:11,540
You have no allies here.

254
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:14,001
Do this for your father.

255
00:13:14,877 --> 00:13:16,712
Defeat me later.

256
00:13:16,795 --> 00:13:19,298
When you get out of here, find Ibyang.

257
00:13:20,257 --> 00:13:24,011
[stirring music continues]

258
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:30,267
[suave music playing]

259
00:13:35,272 --> 00:13:36,649
[squelching]

260
00:13:46,909 --> 00:13:52,164
[brazen music playing]

261
00:14:01,257 --> 00:14:02,341
[groovy ambient music playing]

262
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:03,926
[rich patron] What now?!

263
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:07,096
- [rich patron] Is everyone here?
- [employee] Yes, sir.

264
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:09,515
Only one janitor is missing.

265
00:14:09,598 --> 00:14:11,517
Our guys are looking for him.

266
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:15,020
[employee] Did you see that janitor here?

267
00:14:15,104 --> 00:14:17,064
His name is Jeffrey Matulak.

268
00:14:17,147 --> 00:14:20,192
[janitor] I really can't find him.
Earlier, he was just in the locker room.

269
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:22,528
[employee] Open your eyes.
He's still inside.

270
00:14:27,825 --> 00:14:32,246
[stirring music playing]

271
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:41,255
Bro.

272
00:14:48,637 --> 00:14:49,471
- PJ.
- [light music playing]

273
00:14:54,852 --> 00:14:57,313
Do you know where the girl
we played against earlier lives?

274
00:14:57,396 --> 00:15:00,316
Karla, the one who beat us?

275
00:15:00,399 --> 00:15:02,943
Karla? More like Karlo.

276
00:15:03,027 --> 00:15:04,570
You really had to remind me.

277
00:15:04,653 --> 00:15:07,114
We really got crushed.
No, but I know where that one lives.

278
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:12,745
[dreamy music playing]

279
00:15:15,623 --> 00:15:16,999
Where's my cap?

280
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:22,630
[Karla] Oh, no, I think I left it
at the court. No cap.

281
00:15:22,713 --> 00:15:25,674
Wishful thinking. It's because
you don't take care of your stuff.

282
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:28,594
Mom, it's hard to play basketball
wearing a cap, you know.

283
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:31,347
Sir Delfin gave that to me.

284
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,932
I hope it's still there.

285
00:15:33,807 --> 00:15:36,393
Mom, I'll go out for a bit, okay?
I'll go get my cap.

286
00:15:36,477 --> 00:15:37,978
Make sure that's the only place
you're going, okay?

287
00:15:38,062 --> 00:15:39,730
- [Cita] It's late. Come home right away.
- [Karla] Okay.

288
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:41,023
There's a rumble at the corner!

289
00:15:41,106 --> 00:15:43,150
Emerson and Bunda Girl
are being ganged up on!

290
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:45,361
- [Karla] Oh, no! Let's go, let's go!
- [Tonet] Miss Cita, I need to go there!

291
00:15:45,444 --> 00:15:47,529
Stay here, okay? Lock the door.

292
00:15:47,613 --> 00:15:49,448
Don't let anyone in, okay?

293
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:51,158
Be careful.

294
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:53,494
Lock this! Lock it now. Go on!

295
00:15:53,577 --> 00:15:54,745
Lock it, Ibyang!

296
00:15:56,246 --> 00:16:01,293
[tense music continues]

297
00:16:07,257 --> 00:16:10,094
- Boss, one order of siomai.
- All right.

298
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:11,261
What's happening there?

299
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:12,513
Is there a robbery?

300
00:16:12,596 --> 00:16:13,722
It's chaos out there.

301
00:16:13,806 --> 00:16:16,892
Looks like the new janitor
they're accusing of stealing

302
00:16:16,976 --> 00:16:18,060
from a customer managed to escape.

303
00:16:18,143 --> 00:16:19,853
- [vendor] Oh?
- [security] Mmm-hmm.

304
00:16:19,937 --> 00:16:21,105
Really?

305
00:16:21,772 --> 00:16:22,773
What was taken?

306
00:16:22,856 --> 00:16:26,902
An expensive watch, but it was returned.

307
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:29,863
Maybe he got scared and backed out.

308
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:33,033
[vendor] Oh? With so many of them there,
he still escaped?

309
00:16:33,117 --> 00:16:34,868
[security] Exactly. I don't know.

310
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:38,288
[inquisitive music playing]

311
00:16:38,372 --> 00:16:40,416
- [security] Where, bro?
- [vendor] There.

312
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,043
[security] Okay, that's fine, boss.

313
00:16:48,090 --> 00:16:49,258
[Ibyang] <i>Let's eat first!</i>

314
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:52,511
We haven't even ordered here yet.

315
00:16:52,594 --> 00:16:54,430
Siomai is my favorite.

316
00:16:58,809 --> 00:17:00,686
Boss, I'll get takeout.

317
00:17:00,769 --> 00:17:02,813
- [vendor] One, boss?
- No, three.

318
00:17:02,896 --> 00:17:03,981
[vendor] Okay, boss.

319
00:17:04,648 --> 00:17:06,734
[bright music playing]

320
00:17:24,793 --> 00:17:29,506
[mellow music playing]

321
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:34,887
[cheeky music playing]

322
00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:40,726
You're really beautiful, Ibyang.

323
00:17:42,728 --> 00:17:43,979
Beautiful.

324
00:17:46,982 --> 00:17:48,525
But stubborn.

325
00:17:49,443 --> 00:17:52,988
But at least, we're not cruel

326
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:55,157
like the others out there.

327
00:17:59,203 --> 00:18:00,245
[scoffs]

328
00:18:01,163 --> 00:18:03,207
This suits me.

329
00:18:04,374 --> 00:18:06,335
[clicking and clacking]

330
00:18:06,418 --> 00:18:07,586
[electronic blipping]

331
00:18:11,131 --> 00:18:14,259
[curious music playing]

332
00:18:19,223 --> 00:18:20,307
What is this?

333
00:18:21,517 --> 00:18:22,893
Bat cave?

334
00:18:22,976 --> 00:18:25,562
[curious music continues]

335
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:27,189
[electronic blipping]

336
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:37,449
[clamoring]

337
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:39,284
What's happening here?

338
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:42,162
Hey! Stop it!

339
00:18:42,246 --> 00:18:44,873
- [clamoring]
- [thudding]

340
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:45,999
Stop it!

341
00:18:46,959 --> 00:18:48,669
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

342
00:18:48,752 --> 00:18:52,339
[Cita] Karla! Karla! Karla!

343
00:18:52,422 --> 00:18:55,884
Karla! Karla! Karla!

344
00:18:56,677 --> 00:18:57,970
[clamoring]

345
00:18:58,053 --> 00:18:59,471
Hey!

346
00:18:59,555 --> 00:19:00,597
What's this chaos?!

347
00:19:01,265 --> 00:19:03,058
[clamoring continues]

348
00:19:03,142 --> 00:19:05,978
Hey! That's enough. Stop it. Stop it!

349
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:07,729
That's enough! That's enough!

350
00:19:08,522 --> 00:19:10,649
- [Paldo] Enough!
- [clamoring continues]

351
00:19:10,732 --> 00:19:12,776
[Paldo] Enough!

352
00:19:12,860 --> 00:19:14,945
[Paldo] Stop it! Stop it!

353
00:19:15,028 --> 00:19:17,030
[clamoring continues]

354
00:19:17,114 --> 00:19:20,284
[man] Karla! Enough! Stop it!

355
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:24,079
Hey! What's going on?!

356
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:25,455
You're just meddling!

357
00:19:25,539 --> 00:19:27,249
You're all outsiders!

358
00:19:27,332 --> 00:19:29,459
- [gun firing]
- [Mongki screaming]

359
00:19:29,543 --> 00:19:31,295
What?! Huh?!

360
00:19:31,378 --> 00:19:33,463
Who else is brave here?! What?!

361
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:36,592
[breathing heavily]

362
00:19:36,675 --> 00:19:38,635
[Cita whimpering]

363
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:43,932
What?! You think you're tough?!
Where's your cojones?!

364
00:19:44,016 --> 00:19:46,894
I'm only looking
for one person here! Atoy!

365
00:19:46,977 --> 00:19:49,062
So, if you don't want
to get dragged into this,

366
00:19:49,146 --> 00:19:50,981
just answer me!

367
00:19:51,064 --> 00:19:52,357
- Bro, bro…
- [indistinct chattering]

368
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:53,942
Bro, wait, calm down.

369
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:55,569
Calm down, calm down.

370
00:19:55,652 --> 00:19:59,740
The person you're looking for
isn't here anymore.

371
00:20:00,949 --> 00:20:02,326
Where is he? Where?

372
00:20:03,035 --> 00:20:04,161
He moved to another place.

373
00:20:04,244 --> 00:20:05,704
I don't know where.
He didn't say anything.

374
00:20:05,787 --> 00:20:06,830
[Mongki] Huh?

375
00:20:07,414 --> 00:20:08,790
He's right.

376
00:20:09,625 --> 00:20:13,795
Atoy hasn't been here
since his father died.

377
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:20,469
[Peping] It's better if you leave now.

378
00:20:21,303 --> 00:20:23,430
Sorry if anyone got hurt.

379
00:20:23,513 --> 00:20:25,599
The people here are decent.

380
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:27,434
Leave now, Kuya Mongki.

381
00:20:29,186 --> 00:20:30,812
Sorry for the trouble.

382
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:32,731
They won't come back here again.

383
00:20:34,566 --> 00:20:35,817
Go now, Big Bro Mongki.

384
00:20:36,443 --> 00:20:38,028
[Emerson] Wait, wait, wait!

385
00:20:38,111 --> 00:20:39,821
What? That's it?

386
00:20:39,905 --> 00:20:42,950
You should have
these troublemakers arrested!

387
00:20:43,033 --> 00:20:44,826
- They just caused us problems here!
- [clamoring]

388
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:46,662
They even threatened us, didn't they?

389
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:48,247
- He's dangerous!
- [man] Wait, wait.

390
00:20:48,330 --> 00:20:50,207
If you report that to the police,
they might come after you.

391
00:20:50,290 --> 00:20:51,124
He has a gun.

392
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:52,334
[man] That's true.

393
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:54,836
Ah, well… Just pay us instead!

394
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,338
- Oh, yes, just pay us!
- [clamoring]

395
00:20:56,421 --> 00:20:57,631
[Gavin] Okay, okay!

396
00:20:57,714 --> 00:21:00,050
I'll take care of it.

397
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:03,679
But I only brought a little money.

398
00:21:06,139 --> 00:21:07,266
Ten thousand pesos?

399
00:21:08,183 --> 00:21:09,518
- Maybe this will do?
- [suave music playing]

400
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:11,311
- Is that too little?
- [Gavin] I'm really sorry.

401
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:13,313
Sorry.

402
00:21:13,397 --> 00:21:15,357
That's how it is when you're a nepo baby!

403
00:21:16,650 --> 00:21:20,237
Add 5,000 more
because you slammed me down!

404
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,531
[man] You slammed her, huh!

405
00:21:22,614 --> 00:21:24,241
- [funky music playing]
- I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

406
00:21:24,324 --> 00:21:25,742
I didn't want this to happen.

407
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:28,453
But fine.

408
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:32,749
- Fifteen thousand.
- [Emerson] Whoo!

409
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:34,960
[funky music playing]

410
00:21:37,212 --> 00:21:40,048
- Fifteen thousand. I'm really sorry.
- [Emerson mumbles]

411
00:21:40,132 --> 00:21:41,216
That might be enough.

412
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:43,510
[Paldo] Are you hurt, bro? Huh?

413
00:21:43,593 --> 00:21:44,970
- [Paldo] Does it hurt anywhere, bro?
- [Emerson] Yes.

414
00:21:45,053 --> 00:21:46,680
[Emerson] This 15,000 isn't enough.

415
00:21:46,763 --> 00:21:49,808
No, no, this isn't for you. Not for you.

416
00:21:49,891 --> 00:21:52,978
[Paldo] Father. You take this.

417
00:21:55,355 --> 00:21:57,983
- [Gavin] I'm sorry, really sorry.
- [Bunda] Father, please.

418
00:21:58,066 --> 00:21:59,776
Our goods were damaged.

419
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:01,737
[Peping] Cita, it's your turn.

420
00:22:01,820 --> 00:22:04,156
[Paldo] Are we okay? Are we okay now?

421
00:22:05,032 --> 00:22:07,701
Please, let's not make this bigger, okay?

422
00:22:07,784 --> 00:22:09,369
They already apologized.

423
00:22:09,453 --> 00:22:12,164
That's enough. I'll send them away, okay?

424
00:22:12,247 --> 00:22:13,999
That's enough, that's enough.

425
00:22:14,082 --> 00:22:15,167
[Paldo] Go now, go now. Leave.

426
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:16,376
- [Gavin] Sorry.
- [crowd buzzing]

427
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:18,337
[woman] Our goods.

428
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:21,465
- [woman 1] It's your fault.
- [woman 2] What about our goods?

429
00:22:21,548 --> 00:22:24,092
[indistinct chattering]

430
00:22:24,176 --> 00:22:27,888
[somber music playing]

431
00:22:31,475 --> 00:22:35,145
Oh, even if what happened
to us earlier wasn't pleasant,

432
00:22:35,228 --> 00:22:40,317
I'm still glad because I saw the unity
of the residents against them.

433
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:43,445
That's right, Father.
I really don't know any of them.

434
00:22:44,696 --> 00:22:46,448
Most likely, after what happened earlier,

435
00:22:46,531 --> 00:22:48,241
they won't do anything nice
to Big Brother Atoy.

436
00:22:48,325 --> 00:22:51,411
So, it was right that we covered for Atoy.

437
00:22:52,829 --> 00:22:53,789
- Father.
- Oh?

438
00:22:53,872 --> 00:22:55,415
[inquisitive music playing]

439
00:22:55,499 --> 00:22:58,043
What did you cover up?

440
00:22:58,126 --> 00:22:59,086
What's going on?

441
00:22:59,169 --> 00:23:01,963
Big Brother, some outsiders
came earlier, three men.

442
00:23:02,047 --> 00:23:03,632
They were causing trouble.
They were looking for you.

443
00:23:07,094 --> 00:23:08,845
Did anyone get hurt?

444
00:23:08,929 --> 00:23:13,100
Oh, thank God no one was seriously hurt.

445
00:23:13,725 --> 00:23:14,684
Seriously?

446
00:23:15,852 --> 00:23:18,188
‘Nang, do you know them?

447
00:23:18,271 --> 00:23:23,777
I don't know them, Atoy,
but I heard the name of one. Mongki?

448
00:23:24,903 --> 00:23:26,488
[Mongki] I'll take care of this, Boss.

449
00:23:26,571 --> 00:23:30,742
[grunting]

450
00:23:30,826 --> 00:23:33,203
Should we be worried, Atoy?

451
00:23:34,996 --> 00:23:35,872
No.

452
00:23:36,706 --> 00:23:37,874
Don't worry.

453
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:39,835
It won't happen again.

454
00:23:41,419 --> 00:23:42,546
Is Ibyang here?

455
00:23:42,629 --> 00:23:45,590
Oh, Atoy, you're here.

456
00:23:46,633 --> 00:23:48,635
Manang, I really can't find Ibyang,

457
00:23:48,718 --> 00:23:50,387
- not in the kitchen or the bathroom.
- Huh?

458
00:23:51,263 --> 00:23:52,806
Why? Karla, what?

459
00:23:52,889 --> 00:23:54,808
Did Ibyang escape from you again?
Where is she?

460
00:23:54,891 --> 00:23:57,310
How should I know, Brother!
I didn't see her!

461
00:23:57,936 --> 00:23:59,604
When the commotion broke out,

462
00:23:59,688 --> 00:24:00,772
I told her to stay.

463
00:24:00,856 --> 00:24:02,941
I said, lock the door
and don't let anyone in.

464
00:24:03,817 --> 00:24:05,986
When we got back, the door was locked.

465
00:24:06,695 --> 00:24:10,699
[stirring music continues]

466
00:24:11,533 --> 00:24:14,369
[electronic blipping]

467
00:24:17,330 --> 00:24:21,668
[intense music playing]

468
00:24:21,751 --> 00:24:24,045
Looks like Ame was brought
into underground fighting.

469
00:24:24,129 --> 00:24:26,131
- Poor girl.
- [Atoy] Indeed.

470
00:24:26,214 --> 00:24:27,924
[Atoy] <i>I already have a way to get inside.</i>

471
00:24:28,550 --> 00:24:29,509
[in English] Hi, sir! Good evening!

472
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:30,635
[in English] Good evening.

473
00:24:30,719 --> 00:24:32,345
A client spoke to me.

474
00:24:32,429 --> 00:24:33,346
Why?

475
00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:37,726
He wants to take me to Japan
for his customer,

476
00:24:37,809 --> 00:24:39,060
but I have a bad feeling about it.

477
00:24:39,144 --> 00:24:42,981
[in English] I want to put all my money
on this fighter.

478
00:24:43,064 --> 00:24:44,065
Uh-huh.

479
00:24:44,149 --> 00:24:45,775
Amazing Ame.

480
00:24:45,859 --> 00:24:49,070
[MC] This time, they will be fighting

481
00:24:49,154 --> 00:24:55,035
two of our most beloved patrons!

482
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:56,870
We're at a disadvantage.

483
00:24:56,953 --> 00:24:58,830
UP NEXT

484
00:24:59,581 --> 00:25:00,707
You're all disgusting.

485
00:25:01,666 --> 00:25:03,084
Keep quiet.

486
00:25:04,044 --> 00:25:05,503
I'm a friend of Ibyang.

487
00:25:13,887 --> 00:25:15,555
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
